00:00:14.779 --> 00:00:17.680
In fact, even for our missions conference this year,

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:19.200
we kept the same theme

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:22.159
because we wanna keep ingrained in our minds

00:00:22.159 --> 00:00:24.319
the importance of continuing

00:00:24.319 --> 00:00:26.959
and to continue to serve the Lord,

00:00:26.959 --> 00:00:29.959
to remain faithful in the midst of opposition

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:32.080
and adversity and all that we would face,

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:34.180
that our eyes are on Jesus,

00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:35.639
we're looking unto Jesus,

00:00:35.639 --> 00:00:37.799
the author and finisher of our faith.

00:00:37.799 --> 00:00:40.520
We find that the apostle Paul is used of God

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:45.520
in 1 and 2 Timothy to encourage his son in the faith,

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:48.880
as he's referred to, to continue.

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:51.520
And he tells them in this particular book

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.959
in 2 Timothy, we'll get there in a few,

00:00:53.959 --> 00:00:55.360
probably a couple of months,

00:00:55.360 --> 00:00:57.080
in 2 Timothy chapter number three,

00:00:57.119 --> 00:01:00.240
he tells them about the last days that we're living in

00:01:00.240 --> 00:01:01.599
and the perilous times

00:01:01.599 --> 00:01:04.620
and all the characteristics of those days.

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:07.639
And he says that evil men and seducers

00:01:07.639 --> 00:01:09.160
shall wax worse and worse,

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:11.720
deceiving and being deceived,

00:01:11.720 --> 00:01:15.360
but continue and don't give up,

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.419
don't throw in the towel,

00:01:17.419 --> 00:01:20.400
continue, remain steadfast, unmovable,

00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:22.440
always abounding in the work of the Lord.

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:23.279
Why?

00:01:23.279 --> 00:01:27.919
For we know that our labor is not in vain in the Lord.

00:01:27.919 --> 00:01:31.000
And what a joy, as we enter into the second book,

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.800
the second letter, 2 Timothy chapter number one,

00:01:33.800 --> 00:01:36.360
we'll just be looking at two verses this morning.

00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:39.239
And we note the similarities and the greetings

00:01:39.239 --> 00:01:42.879
in 1 Timothy, 2 Timothy, and also in the book of Titus.

00:01:42.879 --> 00:01:45.599
These three books or three letters

00:01:45.599 --> 00:01:50.400
are often referred to as the pastoral epistles.

00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:52.760
We think about these three particular letters

00:01:53.239 --> 00:01:56.120
and we find that as Paul would have it,

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:59.120
of course, all scripture is given by inspiration of God,

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:02.680
but as Paul would be writing to Timothy and to Titus,

00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:05.800
he refers to both of them as being his son.

00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:10.080
Now, they're not his son biologically or physically,

00:02:10.080 --> 00:02:13.779
but we understand that spiritually speaking,

00:02:13.779 --> 00:02:17.360
the apostle Paul had a great relationship

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:19.919
with both Timothy and Titus.

00:02:19.919 --> 00:02:21.720
I believe that that relationship

00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:24.199
with these younger servants of the Lord

00:02:24.199 --> 00:02:27.440
was both special and unique.

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:30.839
I believe that the apostle Paul in his heart

00:02:30.839 --> 00:02:34.279
had a special place for Timothy and for Titus.

00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:38.720
And I think that Titus and Timothy also held in their heart

00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:42.240
a special place for Paul and all the influence

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:44.360
that he had upon their lives.

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:47.360
In fact, it's interesting to note how Paul,

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:50.880
yes, he encourages many that he writes to

00:02:50.919 --> 00:02:53.679
with regard to how he's praying for them,

00:02:53.679 --> 00:02:55.759
but I think about these individuals,

00:02:55.759 --> 00:03:00.460
Timothy and Titus engaged in the work of the ministry

00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:05.460
as pastors that God would use Paul to encourage them

00:03:05.559 --> 00:03:09.419
and to remind them that he's praying for them.

00:03:09.419 --> 00:03:12.139
And what a tremendous blessing that is.

00:03:12.139 --> 00:03:14.360
Paul, of course, through these two books,

00:03:14.360 --> 00:03:18.759
specifically dealing with the life and ministry of Timothy,

00:03:18.759 --> 00:03:22.320
Paul would be used of the Lord to both instruct

00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:25.059
and encourage Timothy.

00:03:25.059 --> 00:03:27.000
We find that he'll be used of the Lord

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:28.800
in the book of Titus to, again,

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:31.600
both instruct and encourage Titus.

00:03:31.600 --> 00:03:34.039
But what was Paul's desire?

00:03:34.039 --> 00:03:37.479
I believe that Paul desired that these men,

00:03:37.479 --> 00:03:40.279
that Timothy, in the context of what we're looking at

00:03:40.279 --> 00:03:41.800
this calendar year,

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:45.419
that Timothy would serve the Lord faithfully,

00:03:45.419 --> 00:03:49.779
that Timothy would serve God all the days of his life,

00:03:49.779 --> 00:03:53.339
that he would be able to say, as Paul will say

00:03:53.339 --> 00:03:56.020
in this particular letter in the fourth chapter,

00:03:56.020 --> 00:03:57.339
that I have finished.

00:03:57.339 --> 00:04:01.460
I've come to the end and I fought a good fight.

00:04:01.460 --> 00:04:04.580
I kept the faith and what a joy.

00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:06.880
And I believe that that's Paul's desire.

00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:09.720
So Paul, understanding all of the circumstances

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:11.639
of what was taking place at Ephesus

00:04:11.639 --> 00:04:13.979
with regard to the false teaching

00:04:14.300 --> 00:04:17.140
and all of the opposition

00:04:17.140 --> 00:04:19.220
that Timothy would be dealing with,

00:04:19.220 --> 00:04:21.700
God understands that as well.

00:04:21.700 --> 00:04:25.000
And therefore, God would send and use Paul

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:28.760
to write these letters to be a blessing

00:04:28.760 --> 00:04:30.899
and an encouragement to Timothy.

00:04:30.899 --> 00:04:33.739
We find that this letter that is before us this morning

00:04:33.739 --> 00:04:38.019
is the final letter that we have of the Apostle Paul.

00:04:38.019 --> 00:04:42.940
We do not know with certainty how many weeks, months

00:04:42.940 --> 00:04:46.059
took place between the writing of this letter

00:04:46.059 --> 00:04:48.179
and Paul's death.

00:04:48.179 --> 00:04:51.140
But we know that it was within this short period of time

00:04:51.140 --> 00:04:53.239
that after Paul wrote this letter,

00:04:53.239 --> 00:04:55.619
that Paul would face a martyr's death,

00:04:55.619 --> 00:04:59.260
that he would die for his faith in Christ Jesus.

00:04:59.260 --> 00:05:00.739
And as we look at this passage,

00:05:00.739 --> 00:05:02.619
notice with me in chapter one,

00:05:02.619 --> 00:05:04.579
we're just gonna look at verses one and two.

00:05:04.579 --> 00:05:05.500
The Bible says this,

00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:09.820
Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ,

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:12.059
by the will of God,

00:05:12.059 --> 00:05:15.140
according to the promise of life,

00:05:15.140 --> 00:05:18.739
