00:05:52.660 --> 00:05:54.899
And I just have two thoughts for you this morning,

00:05:54.899 --> 00:05:57.100
but remember, just because there's two points

00:05:57.100 --> 00:05:58.940
doesn't mean it's gonna be any shorter.

00:05:58.940 --> 00:06:01.440
And first point this morning, if you're taking notes,

00:06:01.440 --> 00:06:02.579
the first thought is this,

00:06:02.579 --> 00:06:05.859
notice what Paul acknowledged.

00:06:05.859 --> 00:06:08.380
As we look at these two verses of scripture,

00:06:08.420 --> 00:06:11.320
we find that Paul acknowledged some things

00:06:11.320 --> 00:06:14.100
that are important not only for Paul,

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:15.579
they're important for Timothy,

00:06:15.579 --> 00:06:17.660
but they're important for each of us as well.

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:19.220
As the people of God,

00:06:19.220 --> 00:06:21.700
there are some things that we must acknowledge

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:23.019
or recognize.

00:06:23.019 --> 00:06:25.299
And we find in the text of scripture,

00:06:25.299 --> 00:06:29.899
number one, that Paul acknowledged the authority of God.

00:06:29.899 --> 00:06:31.299
Notice in verse number one,

00:06:31.299 --> 00:06:35.619
the Bible says Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ,

00:06:35.619 --> 00:06:37.899
by the will of God.

00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:40.260
And we find that the apostle Paul,

00:06:40.260 --> 00:06:43.179
he understood who he was,

00:06:43.179 --> 00:06:46.059
and he understood who God is.

00:06:46.059 --> 00:06:48.359
I believe that if we begin to understand

00:06:48.359 --> 00:06:51.459
how that Paul acknowledges the authority of God,

00:06:51.459 --> 00:06:55.179
even in the greeting that he writes to Timothy,

00:06:55.179 --> 00:06:58.380
that it's crucial, it's absolutely imperative,

00:06:58.380 --> 00:07:01.160
it is critical for every child of God

00:07:01.160 --> 00:07:05.859
to acknowledge God's authority in our lives.

00:07:05.859 --> 00:07:09.940
See, the reality is that we have this society

00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:12.700
and this culture has almost ingrained

00:07:12.700 --> 00:07:16.619
in the minds of people that you are your own authority

00:07:16.619 --> 00:07:19.140
and you are the one that determines

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:20.899
and you make the decision.

00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:22.739
But as a child of God,

00:07:22.739 --> 00:07:25.779
I understand that Paul says to the believers in Corinth

00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:28.299
in chapter number six of the first letter he writes them

00:07:28.299 --> 00:07:29.700
in first Corinthians six,

00:07:29.700 --> 00:07:30.540
what?

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:33.220
Know ye not that what?

00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:35.540
Your body is the temple of the Holy Ghost,

00:07:36.220 --> 00:07:37.739
which is in you what you have of God,

00:07:37.739 --> 00:07:41.940
and ye are not your own,

00:07:41.940 --> 00:07:43.459
for you are bought with a price.

00:07:43.459 --> 00:07:45.940
Therefore, we're to glorify God.

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:46.779
How?

00:07:46.779 --> 00:07:50.540
In every way, in every part of my being,

00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:52.299
I am to glorify God.

00:07:52.299 --> 00:07:53.140
Why?

00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:54.079
Because he owns me.

00:07:55.239 --> 00:07:56.420
It's a matter of authority.

00:07:56.420 --> 00:07:58.339
It's a matter of ownership.

00:07:58.339 --> 00:08:01.299
And we find this morning as we look at this truth

00:08:01.299 --> 00:08:02.579
as the apostle Paul,

00:08:02.579 --> 00:08:05.700
he's acknowledged the authority of God in his life.

00:08:05.700 --> 00:08:08.260
Understand with me that the apostle Paul,

00:08:08.260 --> 00:08:10.179
before his name was ever Paul,

00:08:10.179 --> 00:08:12.779
we know him as Saul.

00:08:12.779 --> 00:08:15.339
And we understand that Saul was a man

00:08:15.339 --> 00:08:17.059
that was a religious man.

00:08:17.059 --> 00:08:20.220
Saul was a man that knew the Old Testament.

00:08:20.220 --> 00:08:23.679
I mean, he was trained by the best of the best.

00:08:23.679 --> 00:08:26.859
He was extremely familiar with Judaism

00:08:26.859 --> 00:08:28.339
and all of its ins and outs.

00:08:28.339 --> 00:08:30.380
And he was a religious man,

00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:32.940
but as he's going and persecuting

00:08:32.940 --> 00:08:35.979
and giving consent to the death of Stephen

00:08:35.979 --> 00:08:37.419
and all that he's doing,

00:08:37.419 --> 00:08:39.059
he has letters in his hand.

00:08:39.059 --> 00:08:42.539
He has the authority that he could go

00:08:42.539 --> 00:08:47.059
and put to death to imprison any that be of this way

00:08:47.059 --> 00:08:50.539
or of that way, that being Christians.

00:08:50.539 --> 00:08:53.500
We find that the apostle Paul,

00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:55.700
at that point, his name is Saul.

00:08:55.700 --> 00:08:57.419
He meets Jesus.

00:08:58.419 --> 00:09:01.739
In Acts chapter number nine, it's recorded for us.

00:09:01.739 --> 00:09:04.299
The Bible says that he sees this bright light

00:09:04.299 --> 00:09:05.900
and he hears a voice.

00:09:05.900 --> 00:09:09.739
And the voice is, Saul, Saul,

00:09:09.739 --> 00:09:12.460
why persecutest thou me?

00:09:12.460 --> 00:09:15.940
And we find that Saul answers and says,

00:09:15.940 --> 00:09:19.179
who art thou, Lord?

00:09:20.659 --> 00:09:24.820
I am Jesus, whom thou persecutest.

00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:26.919
It is hard for thee to kick against the pricks.

00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:29.119
There was a measure of conviction

00:09:29.119 --> 00:09:31.799
that was coming in Saul's life.

00:09:31.799 --> 00:09:34.840
And then Saul follows up the question

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.559
of who art thou, Lord, with this,

00:09:37.559 --> 00:09:40.840
Lord, what wilt thou have me to do?

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:42.200
Isn't that amazing?

00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:45.559
To consider immediately upon salvation

00:09:45.559 --> 00:09:48.559
how the apostle Paul, in that moment,

00:09:48.559 --> 00:09:52.400
he acknowledged, he recognized the authority of God

00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:55.919
in his life that he's going with a certain purpose,

00:09:55.919 --> 00:09:57.599
with a certain agenda.

00:09:57.599 --> 00:09:59.799
But his life is transformed.

00:09:59.799 --> 00:10:03.239
If any man be in Christ, he is a new creature.

00:10:03.239 --> 00:10:04.539
Old things are passed away.

00:10:04.539 --> 00:10:06.439
Behold, all things are become new.

00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:10.159
And we find that this man, after his conversion,

00:10:10.159 --> 00:10:16.579
he says, Lord, what will Thou have me to do?

00:10:16.579 --> 00:10:19.919
He did not say, now, Lord, here's what I plan to do.

00:10:19.919 --> 00:10:22.519
He didn't say, now, Lord, here's my ability.

00:10:22.519 --> 00:10:23.879
Here's my talent.

00:10:23.879 --> 00:10:27.679
Here's how you, God, can use me.

00:10:27.679 --> 00:10:33.639
No, he said, Lord, what will Thou have me to do?

00:10:33.639 --> 00:10:38.119
Now, God used the apostle Paul in a mighty way.

00:10:38.119 --> 00:10:42.399
God used Paul to establish churches and regions

00:10:42.399 --> 00:10:44.719
where the gospel had not yet been.

00:10:44.719 --> 00:10:48.159
He used Paul to stand before leaders,

00:10:48.159 --> 00:10:52.039
both religious and political, and to profess

00:10:52.039 --> 00:10:54.639
the gospel of Jesus Christ.

00:10:54.639 --> 00:10:58.399
But I believe that no matter, as we look at the life of Paul,

00:10:58.399 --> 00:11:01.279
I believe that no matter what God would have assigned him

00:11:01.279 --> 00:11:04.239
to do, he would have willingly done it.

00:11:04.239 --> 00:11:05.719
Why?

00:11:05.719 --> 00:11:08.279
